MAMELODI Sundowns coach Pitso Mosimane has sent a message to all South Africans amid the COVID-19 lockdown. With more than 600 000 confirmed cases worldwide, the world is in war against an "invisible enemy", which has taken thousands of lives globally. Worldwide, sports has been affected by this virus with some athletes testing positive. Mosimane has sent heartfelt message of encouragement to the health staff, police and all essential workers entrusted to care for those who have been infected by the coronavirus. Mamelodi Sundowns coach Pitso Mosimane has sent message of encouragement to health staff, police and all workers entrusted to take care for those who are infected by the Coronavirus. pic.twitter.com/AKKAZl3GGQ 